(17, 'Home', 0, 'Home', '', NULL, NULL, 'home', 'Pages/pagetemplates/home', 0, NULL, '', '', '', '<h2>Intelligent Analytical Modeler&trade;</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class="boxes">\r\n<div class="box first"><img alt="" src="http://datanomers.checkyourprojects.com/app/webroot/ck_files/images/image-1.jpg" />\r\n<h2>Intelligent Analytical Modeler&trade;</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>IAM &trade; is a tool that generates accurate statistical models for predictive analytics.</p>\r\n<a href="{intelligent-analytical-modeler}">Learn More</a></div>\r\n<!--end box-->\r\n\r\n<div class="box"><img alt="" src="http://datanomers.checkyourprojects.com/app/webroot/ck_files/images/image-2.jpg" />\r\n<h2>Enterprise Quality Solutions</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>This solution suite provides a comprehensive call quality measure for end-to-end user experience - QUES.</p>\r\n<a href="{enterprise-quality-solutions}">Learn More</a></div>\r\n<!--end box-->\r\n\r\n<div class="box last"><img alt="" src="http://datanomers.checkyourprojects.com/app/webroot/ck_files/images/image-3.jpg" />\r\n<h2>Fraud Management Solutions</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>This suite of solutions detects and remediates Fraud with 95% accuracy</p>\r\n<a href="{fraud-management}">Learn More</a></div>\r\n<!--end box--></div>\r\n\r\n<div class="boxes">\r\n<div class="box first"><img alt="" src="http://datanomers.checkyourprojects.com/app/webroot/ck_files/images/image-4.jpg" />\r\n<h2>Sales Intelligence Tool</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>This tool intelligently identifies sales opportunities and boosts revenues.</p>\r\n<a href="{sales-intelligence-tool}">Learn More</a></div>\r\n<!--end box-->\r\n\r\n<div class="box"><img alt="" src="http://datanomers.checkyourprojects.com/app/webroot/ck_files/images/image-5.jpg" />\r\n<h2>Unstructured Intelligence Tools</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>This toolset helps mine cognitive insights from unstructured data.</p>\r\n<a href="{unstructured-intelligence-tools}">Learn More</a></div>\r\n<!--end box-->\r\n\r\n<div class="box last"><img alt="" src="http://datanomers.checkyourprojects.com/app/webroot/ck_files/images/image-6.jpg" />\r\n<h2>Professional Services</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Our Professional Services covers the entire gamut - from data gathering for dashboard to predictive analytics.</p>\r\n<a href="{professional-services}">Learn More</a></div>\r\n<!--end box--></div>\r\n', NULL, NULL, 1, '2014-01-16 00:35:52', '2014-01-23 06:37:07'),
(23, 'Voice Quality Manager', 8, 'Voice Quality Manager', '1389857895_1389857895.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'voice-quality-manager', 'pagetemplates/default_template', 0, NULL, '', '', NULL, '<div class="solutions">\r\n<h3>Overview</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Datanomers&rsquo; VQM is a Big Data analytical solution that detects and remediates voice quality in near real time. The solution reduces customer churn and helps you bring in high margin premium traffic for enterprise customers, mobile operators, service providers and wholesale carriers.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>The Challenge</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Voice services are the key to many of the business and consumer transactions.</li>\r\n	<li>Telegeography, an Independent market analysis company has estimated an increase of 5% in international voice traffic and 44% in OTT(Skype-Skype voice and video) traffic .</li>\r\n	<li>Global telecommunication companies are unveiling a raft of next generation voice services like HD voice, Voice over IPX vindicating a movement towards interoperability and voice over IP-based networks.</li>\r\n	<li>Enterprise service providers, Mobile providers, OTTs , whole sale carriers are slugging it out to attract new customers and retain existing customers.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>In this highly competitive voice market with shrinking margins, the differentiator is clear. Reduce customer churn by providing them with the highest quality of service.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>The Solution</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Datanomers Voice Quality Manager is a big data solution that works based off probes and a central management system.<br />\r\nIt accurately measures MOS from loss, jitter, latency for a codec. VQM implements ITU-T G.107 - with accuracy to prevent false positives. VQM measures end to end voice quality.<br />\r\nAccuracy is the hallmark of all Datanomers&#39; solution and VQM is no exception. It is highly accurate and models the de-jitter buffer accurately</p>\r\n\r\n<table align="left" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td class="brown-bg">Features</td>\r\n			<td class="brown-bg">Datanomers Solution</td>\r\n			<td class="brown-bg">Competitor Solutions</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td class="brown-bg">Accuracy</td>\r\n			<td class="grey-bg" valign="top">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>Accurately measures MOS from loss, jitter for a codec</li>\r\n				<li>Measures end to end voice quality</li>\r\n				<li>Models the de-jitter buffer accurately</li>\r\n				<li>Implements ITU-T G.107 with accuracy</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td class="grey-bg" valign="top">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>Does not measure end to end voice quality</li>\r\n				<li>MOS is just measured for the IP leg</li>\r\n				<li>Implements P.862&rsquo;s PESQ which doesn&rsquo;t consider letency</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td class="brown-bg">Coverage</td>\r\n			<td valign="top">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li><u>Measures the quality of a interactive voice conversation accurately</u></li>\r\n				<li><u>Measures latency accurately</u></li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td valign="top">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>Does not consider latency</li>\r\n				<li>Cannot predict the quality of a interactive voice conversation accurately</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td class="brown-bg">Remediation</td>\r\n			<td class="grey-bg" valign="top">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>Auto-Removal/blockage of fraudulent ranges in near real time</li>\r\n				<li>ACTIONABLE INTELLIGENCE</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td class="grey-bg" valign="top">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>Delays in detection and remediation</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td class="brown-bg">Fault Isolation</td>\r\n			<td valign="top">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>Automates the tedious process of finding where the fault is</li>\r\n				<li><u>ACTIONABLE INTELLIGENCE</u></li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td valign="top">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>Delays in detection and remediation</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td class="brown-bg">Scalability</td>\r\n			<td class="grey-bg" valign="top">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>Scalable solution based on big data analytics</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td class="grey-bg" valign="top">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>Questionable scalability</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td class="brown-bg">Process Improvement</td>\r\n			<td valign="top">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>Email/SNMP notification</li>\r\n				<li>Better Operations KPI</li>\r\n				<li>Better SLAs</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td valign="top">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>Operations team work with a myriad of tools and troubleshooting is slow and tedious</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td class="brown-bg">VQM Dashboard</td>\r\n			<td class="grey-bg" valign="top">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>Customers get a peek on how well quality is monitored.</li>\r\n				<li>Rich set of reporting</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td class="grey-bg" valign="top">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>Basic Reports</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>On the whole, Datanomers Voice quality Manager accurately monitors voice quality and helps intelligently troubleshoot and fix issues.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Contact us at <a href="mailto:sales@datanomers.com"><u>sales@datanomers.com</u></a> for an initial evaluation.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n', NULL, NULL, 1, '2014-01-16 02:38:15', '2014-01-16 04:12:27'),
(24, 'IPX QoS Performance Manager', 8, 'IPX QoS Performance Manager', '1389857958_1389857958.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'IPX-QoS-performance-manager', 'pagetemplates/default_template', 0, NULL, '', '', NULL, '<div class="solutions">\r\n<h3 class="heading-main">IPX QoS Performance Manager</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The promise of IPX technology is to provide richer and higher quality of user experience for the end subscriber. However, keeping the promise is extremely challenging unless rigorous quality management measures are put in place. The measures must comprehensively address the 3 levels of QoS for IPX deployments &ndash; Transport, IPX Service and User Experience.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Transport:</strong> Is the underlying MPLS network delivering the designed packet loss, latency, jitter? Are the different VPNs (e.g. by service, by customer) delivering the required transport service level?</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>IPX Service:</strong> Are the service layers delivering the specified edge to edge service agreed in the SLA? Is this being achieved across peered IPXs?</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>End to End Service:</strong> Is the end user getting the service they expect? Although this might not be SLA, what is being achieved?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>QoS must be monitored and delivered at both transport and service level. Transport paths must be monitored using the paths actually used by service components (not just the IP path) and across peered IPXs. Service monitoring must ensure service delivery across IPX from edge to edge plus acceptable service delivery end to end.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Datanomers&rsquo; IPX QoS Performance Manager</strong> is a comprehensive solution suite that helps manage the quality of service for IPX deployments end to end. The quality of service is assured through combination of probes at edges of IPX platform and deep statistical analysis of call detail records for each service. The suite includes</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>IP-VPN Transport Performance Manager</strong> that deploys proactive probes to monitor each CoS periodically between each pair of POPs (IPX demarcation point). The performance manager alerts if QoS SLAs are violated &ndash; for example, latency SLAs not being achieved because of network failure or congestion. The solution also includes a troubleshooter (fault management) that uses smart probes to pin-point congested IP node.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>IPX Service Performance Manager</strong> that monitors IMS service nodes periodically for each service type, alerting if SLAs associated with service are violated.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div class="full-width-img"><img alt="" src="http://datanomers.checkyourprojects.com/app/webroot/ck_files/images/img-14.png" /></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Intelligent QoS Manager</strong> that provides intelligent insights in the performance behavior of IPX by correlating Transport and service alerts to sectionalize the fault and also provides rich set of reports that graphically describe SLA offenders and their offenses.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>User Experience QoS Manager</strong> provides a measure of end user experience by monitoring call records to determine true customer experience. It considers all the use cases of a call (set up and conversation both) and provides a measure for end-to-end user experience for instance, call disruptions during conversations, excessive retries during call setup - that heavily influence subscriber&#39;s experience of a call much more.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div class="full-width-img"><img alt="" src="http://datanomers.checkyourprojects.com/app/webroot/ck_files/images/img-15.png" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n', NULL, NULL, 1, '2014-01-16 02:39:18', '2014-01-16 04:08:37'),
(25, 'False Answer Supervision', 9, 'False Answer Supervision', '1389858057_1389858057.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'false-answer-supervision', 'pagetemplates/default_template', 0, NULL, '', '', NULL, '<div class="solutions">\r\n<p>The carrier business is competitive: voice products are increasingly commoditized, and margins are getting razor thin. Carriers need to differentiate from their competitors, by providing better, cost-effective, service to high value customers. That&rsquo;s what Datanomer&rsquo;s solutions help you deliver. Datanomers Big Data Solutions are comprehensive and unique: based on expert systems autonomics and cognitive science, are intuitive, accurate and can easily automate complex processes. One such solution is False Answer Supervision. The biggest telecom carriers in the world have benefited financially from the solutions.<br />\r\nOnce you deploy our Fraud Management Solution, you will notice an immediate improvement in route quality. How?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Because, our advanced statistical machine-learning state-of-the-art technology is highly accurate and has global coverage that enables the deployment of our solution to break even in under a year. Your route quality improves substantially as you rid it of fraud. Your customers notice and give you more business, especially for premium traffic with higher margins. Your business differentiates and grows.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>The Challenge</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>What is Fraud and How Does it Afflict Carriers?</strong><br />\r\nFraud has permeated in both carriers and enterprises, bleeding over $6B dollars annually from carriers. The result: Unhappy Customers Switching Carriers, Lost revenue for Carriers because of no fault of their own, Customer churn. Enterprises get unexpected, large bills and demands for payment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Fraud Types</strong><br />\r\nThere are several types of fraud, But most important ones are:<br />\r\n1- False Answer Supervision (FAS),<br />\r\n2- Premium Rate Fraud (IPRF) and<br />\r\n3- Mobile Fraud.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class="left-side"><img alt="" src="http://datanomers.checkyourprojects.com/app/webroot/ck_files/images/img-9.png" /></div>\r\n\r\n<p>FAS is perhaps the most prevalent and is under the control of international carriers. So What is FAS? FAS occurs when a call is falsely answered by a downstream carrier so they can start billing well in advance of the real answer. Even worse for customers is a phenomenon, known as call hijacking, where the call is routed to an automated voice system designed to keep them on the phone while billing continues; not only do they get a huge bill, but the call does not even reach the dialed customer.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>IPRF occurs when a premium rate service provider colludes with a hacker to break into a PBX, launch a large number of calls to an international premium rate destination, get a share of the profits from the distant service provider, and disappear before the break-in is found. The enterprise whose PBX was hacked refuses to pay the bill and carriers in the chain dispute billing, resulting in large losses for all concerned!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mobile Fraud is very damaging to the mobile industry with cloned SIMs and roaming fraud generating many unpaid calls to distant high rate premium codes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="width:100%; float:left;"><strong>Carriers Fight Back</strong><br />\r\nCarriers are now increasingly serious about fighting fraud. They have banded together, under the aegis of the standards i3Forum, to publish a process that removes traffic for weeks from those carriers without efficient fraud management systems, resulting in considerable revenue loss.<br />\r\nIf you don&#39;t police fraud in your network, you risk losing revenue.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="width:100%; float:left;">There are probe based solutions in the market that do not come close to our solution in delivering features and functions and aren&#39;t effective in eradicating FAS. They have their limitations:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul class="int-content">\r\n	<li>In case of probe based solution, you need to have the carrier launch several synthetic calls to a all these destinations. If not FAS goes undetected.</li>\r\n	<li>Fraudsters are getting smart: for example, blended FAS which is done intelligently by the fraudulent suppliers in the network to avoid detection: FAS is switched on and off. for probe&#39;s synthetic calls to detect such blended FAS, the carrier needs to place several test calls to the same destination, daily, and then out of several to a destination, a couple may detect blended FAS. when you have blended FAS happening in the intl destinations, the OPex rises, the solution becomes more expensive than the issue it addresses.</li>\r\n	<li>Probe based solutions cannot handle the volume of CDRs our solution can handle</li>\r\n	<li>Probe based solution cannot accurately quantify fraud. Datanomers&rsquo; statistical solution is not academic. It quantifies fraud. It helps you make decisions to remediate supplier and goes a step further than all other solutions in the market. Our FAS solution stores the cdrs of fraud calls which provides you with the irrefutable evidence that a supplier was doing FAS. Now we can dispute billing w/ suppliers, negotiate better rates with them, trouble shoot the issue, and insist on better quality</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div class="left-side"><img alt="" src="http://datanomers.checkyourprojects.com/app/webroot/ck_files/images/img-10.png" /></div>\r\n\r\n<h3 style="width:100%; float:left;">The Solution</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style="width:100%; float:left;"><strong>Datanomer&rsquo;s Unique Solution</strong><br />\r\nDatanomer&rsquo;s fraud management solutions are the most technologically advanced on the market and some of the largest Global Carriers rely on Datanomer&rsquo;s solution to combat FAS, They statistically identify fraud directly from a carrier&rsquo;s CDRs. These global carriers have expressed <u>tremendous faith in our solutions</u>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="width:100%; float:left;"><strong>Datanomers FAS Solution Differentiator: </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul class="int-content">\r\n	<li>Accuracy of 95% while detecting 90% of the fraud.</li>\r\n	<li>64-Bit industrial server architecture scales to 200M CDRs daily with peak processing rate of 10M CDRs per hour.</li>\r\n	<li>Detects fraud in near real-time. It can easily integrate into your operations systems to stop fraud quickly before it is noticed, reducing customer trouble ticket volume by 15%.</li>\r\n	<li>Stores fraud CDRs so that you can quantify the extent of the fraud, create reports on various suppliers and destinations, and withhold fraudulent payments.</li>\r\n	<li>Covers 100% of worldwide destinations with no extra costs of test calls and probes</li>\r\n	<li>With Datanomers&rsquo; statistical solution, you do not have opex. because it doesn&#39;t generate synthetic calls</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div class="left-side"><img alt="" src="http://datanomers.checkyourprojects.com/app/webroot/ck_files/images/img-11.png" /></div>\r\n\r\n<p class="int-content">Datanomers FAS solution is deployed in your data center managed and administered by you, or as some carriers prefer, in our private cloud and managed and administered by us. Our solution breaks even in under a year, the financials that prove this have been vetted by standards forum and independently verified by carriers</p>\r\n\r\n<div class="left-side"><img alt="" src="http://datanomers.checkyourprojects.com/app/webroot/ck_files/images/img-12.png" /></div>\r\n\r\n<div class="left-side"><img alt="" src="http://datanomers.checkyourprojects.com/app/webroot/ck_files/images/img-13.png" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n', NULL, NULL, 1, '2014-01-16 02:40:57', '2014-01-16 04:41:00'),
(26, 'International Revenue Share Fraud', 9, 'International Revenue Share Fraud', '1389858128_1389858128.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'international-revenue-share-fraud', 'pagetemplates/default_template', 0, NULL, '', '', NULL, '<div class="solutions">\r\n<h3 class="heading-main">Big Data Solution: International Revenue Share Fraud IRSF</h3>\r\n\r\n<h3>Overview</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>International Revenue Share Fraud (IRSF) is one of the most menacing frauds plaguing the telecom industry. IRSF is caused by the artificial inflation of traffic or traffic pumping to the premium rate numbers in the world.<br />\r\nDatanomers&rsquo; International Revenue Share Fraud tool is a big data analytical solution that detects International Revenue Share Fraud (IRSF) and remediates it in near real time which will avert huge financial losses for enterprise customers, mobile operators, service providers and wholesale carriers.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>The Challenge</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>According to the Communications Fraud Control Association (CFCA), telecom industry lost close to <u>$4B billion</u> to revenue share fraud.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Typically IRSF involves a nexus between the following. </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>PRN (Premium Rate Number) Aggregators: who obtain range of fraudulent premium rate numbers (PRN) countries like Lithuania, Sao Tome and enter into an agreement with service providers falsely claiming entertainment services.</li>\r\n	<li>Hackers or the fraudsters who generate traffic. They either hack a PBX of a company, or clone SIM cards and generate millions of artificial calls to premium numbers.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Hackers and the revenue share providers share the revenue generated by the fraudulent calls which will be billed either to the end customer or some carrier in the routing flow.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class="left-side"><img alt="" src="http://datanomers.checkyourprojects.com/app/webroot/ck_files/images/img-6.png" /></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The alarming fact about IRSF is that it is triggered by many other means of fraud like PBX hacking, SIM card cloning, International roaming fraud, subscription theft.</li>\r\n	<li>These premium rate services are the eternal cash cow for the telecom carriers and they are more than willing to buy premium rate services without sufficient checks and balances to distinguish between a rigged and a genuine player.</li>\r\n	<li>The delays in identification of the nature and volume of the calls, delays in blocking the numbers makes IRSF extremely difficult to detect and combat.</li>\r\n	<li>The final straw is the nature of the carrier model, the money transfer has already been done to fraudulent providers who cannot be traced after the fraud has been discovered.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>The Solution</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Datanomers has come up with the state of the art big data analytical solution that detects and remediates IRSF in near real time. Below are</p>\r\n\r\n<table align="left" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td class="brown-bg">Features</td>\r\n			<td class="brown-bg">Datanomers Solution</td>\r\n			<td class="brown-bg">Competitor Solutions</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td class="brown-bg">Accuracy</td>\r\n			<td class="grey-bg" valign="top">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>95% Accuracy</li>\r\n				<li>Patented Algorithms</li>\r\n				<li>Advanced Statistics like <u>Central Limit Theorem, entropy of random variables</u></li>\r\n				<li>Industry Expertise</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td class="grey-bg" valign="top">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>Rely heavily on industry expertise and hot lists of premium service ranges</li>\r\n				<li>Elementary Statistics</li>\r\n				<li>Pre-defined patterns which generates a slew of False positives</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td class="brown-bg">Coverage</td>\r\n			<td valign="top">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>Low Grade IRSF and Blended IRSF are caught in near real time.</li>\r\n				<li>Advanced Machine Learning working off the 200-300 million CDRs</li>\r\n				<li>Algorithms based on Covariance , K-Mean clustering of random variables</li>\r\n				<li>Low-Grade IRSF, Blended IRSF is caught and alerted</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td valign="top">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>Pre-defined pattern to detect</li>\r\n				<li>Missed True positives</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td class="brown-bg">Remediation</td>\r\n			<td class="grey-bg" valign="top">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>Auto-Removal/blockage of fraudulent ranges in near real time</li>\r\n				<li>ACTIONABLE INTELLIGENCE</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td class="grey-bg" valign="top">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>Delays in detection and remediation</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td class="brown-bg">Evidence</td>\r\n			<td valign="top">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>CDR(Call Detail Record) Repository stores fraudulent CDRs as irrefutable evidence</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td valign="top">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>No CDR evidence for missed true positives and wrong CDRs for false</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td class="brown-bg">Scalability</td>\r\n			<td class="grey-bg" valign="top">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>Scalable solution based on big data analytics</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td class="grey-bg" valign="top">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>Questionable scalability</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td class="brown-bg">Process Improvement</td>\r\n			<td valign="top">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>Email/SNMP notification</li>\r\n				<li>Better Operations KPI</li>\r\n				<li>Better SLAs</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td valign="top">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>Operations team work with a myriad of tools and troubleshooting is slow and tedious</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td class="brown-bg">IRSF Dashboard</td>\r\n			<td class="grey-bg" valign="top">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>Customers get a peek on how well fraud is kept under check</li>\r\n				<li>Rich set of reporting</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td class="grey-bg" valign="top">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>Basic Reports</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>In a nutshell Datanomers&rsquo; IRSF solution helps you to Grow business strategically with a quality message. Big deals on the anvil rely on this. Quality is going to be the key in the years to come and Datanomers will help you be the game changer.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n', NULL, NULL, 1, '2014-01-16 02:42:08', '2014-01-16 04:35:15'),
(28, 'Big Value', 0, 'Big Value', '1389869211_1389869211.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'big-value', 'pagetemplates/default_template', 0, NULL, '', '', '', '<p>Datanomers has come up with state-of-the art Intelligent Analytical Modeler&trade; which is based on recent advances in statistics. It defines functions of predictors and correlates them to business outcomes. It addresses all your big data challenges.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We&rsquo;ll delight you with the accuracy of prediction of your business outcomes. We&rsquo;ll collect and sanitize the &ndash; structured and unstructured &ndash; input data, run it through IAM to build an accurate model quickly, and provide professional data scientists to refine the model. All this makes sure that you trust your analytical model and use it to run scenarios to make informed business decisions to outgrow your competitors.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Our Big Differentiator:</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>We couple the three Vs (Volume, Variety, Velocity) with the three As (Automation, Analytics and Accuracy) to provide you with:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Veracity to trust the model to influence your business decisions,</li>\r\n	<li>Automation to keep pace with the dynamics of your business, and</li>\r\n	<li>Actionable intelligence to point out specifics of how you can grow fast.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Skilled data scientists are hard to find and your business decisions are only as good as your predictive model. Our solution does the job of a data scientist &ndash; cost-effectively.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Ecosystem of Solutions offered through IPsoft</h3>\r\n\r\n<div class="full-width-img"><img alt="" src="http://datanomers.checkyourprojects.com/app/webroot/ck_files/images/bid-value-img.png" /></div>\r\n', NULL, NULL, 1, '2014-01-16 05:46:51', '2014-01-16 08:55:51'),
